Good to see you.
-Ah.

14:27.100 --> 14:28.501
-Real good. Real good.
-Yeah. Yeah, yeah.

14:28.535 --> 14:30.770
-You look good.
-You, too. You haven't aged.

14:30.803 --> 14:32.772
-Yeah. Look after yourself.
-Well, yeah.

14:32.805 --> 14:35.142
-It's real good
to see you, mate.
-Talk to you soon.

14:40.080 --> 14:41.448
Now, some of those numbers
aren't gonna add up exactly,

14:41.481 --> 14:42.849
-but I think...
-Some of 'em?

14:42.882 --> 14:44.251
-You know what to do.
-Yeah.

14:44.284 --> 14:45.685
-Some of 'em. Couple of 'em.
-Yeah.

14:45.718 --> 14:47.054
Couple of 'em. Hi, mate.

14:47.087 --> 14:48.855
-You all right?
-Yeah, good.

14:48.888 --> 14:50.790
-You sticking around for a bit?
-Yeah.

14:50.823 --> 14:52.792
I want to talk to you
about something, you know.

14:52.825 --> 14:54.727
-All right.
-How you doing, man?

14:54.761 --> 14:56.196
-Yeah.
-Ray.

14:56.229 --> 14:58.698
-Nasir.
-We got to have a chat,
all right?

14:58.731 --> 15:00.067
I'll catch you later.

15:00.100 --> 15:01.468
-Is that the guy?
-No, mate. Come on.

15:01.501 --> 15:02.869
-Is that the guy?
-Let's go.

15:02.902 --> 15:04.404
Answer me!

15:06.306 --> 15:08.708
I'm gonna teach you about loss.

15:08.741 --> 15:09.776
Excuse me?

15:09.809 --> 15:11.544
-Get to work, please now.
-I know your face now.

15:11.578 --> 15:13.180
-Get to work, Ray!
-Gonna teach you about loss!

15:25.858 --> 15:27.961
-(sighs)
-Davros' brother, was it?

15:27.995 --> 15:30.263
Why the fuck would you
bring him in here?

15:30.297 --> 15:31.965
Yeah, I know, I know.

15:31.999 --> 15:35.235
Hey, listen, um,
that shit he said--

15:35.268 --> 15:36.903
don't worry about that.

15:36.936 --> 15:39.606
He's just...
he's just upset, you know?

15:42.675 --> 15:45.012
Is he a crim?

15:45.045 --> 15:47.014
No. No, he's an accountant.

15:47.047 --> 15:49.782
He's been helping me
with the books.

15:59.526 --> 16:01.961
(dance music playing)

16:05.965 --> 16:08.635
-Yeah.
-I can't even remember

16:08.668 --> 16:10.203
the last time I got laid.

16:10.237 --> 16:12.039
How long's it been?

16:12.072 --> 16:14.174
Oh, shit.

16:14.207 --> 16:15.608
Year and a half, maybe.

16:15.642 --> 16:16.943
Mm.

16:16.976 --> 16:18.211
Well,

16:18.245 --> 16:19.812
I could, uh,

16:19.846 --> 16:21.848
organize something for you,
if you want.

16:21.881 --> 16:23.850
I hate knock shops.

16:23.883 --> 16:25.185
No, I'd just get one
of the girls from work

16:25.218 --> 16:27.354
to come pay you a visit.

16:27.387 --> 16:28.688
BRUCE:
Mm.

16:28.721 --> 16:29.956
Maybe.

16:29.989 --> 16:31.991
Mm.

16:34.994 --> 16:37.364
Can I ask you something?

16:37.397 --> 16:39.532
Yeah.

16:40.567 --> 16:44.371
When I don't feel like doing
any of this anymore,

16:44.404 --> 16:46.339
will you help me?

16:48.375 --> 16:50.977
Help you with what?

16:51.010 --> 16:53.646
You know...

16:53.680 --> 16:56.249
call it quits.

16:59.552 --> 17:01.020
Die?

17:01.054 --> 17:03.456
Yeah.

17:10.897 --> 17:13.166
Cross that bridge
when we come to it, mate, eh?

17:13.200 --> 17:15.602
Yeah, okay.

17:18.571 --> 17:21.074
RAY:
You know, Britt'd miss you.

17:22.775 --> 17:24.844
Yeah, I know.

17:24.877 --> 17:28.014
I'd probably miss you
for about five minutes.

17:28.047 --> 17:29.849
(Bruce chuckles softly)

17:29.882 --> 17:32.285
(birds calling)

17:33.320 --> 17:35.722
You know, you guys
are the only reason

17:35.755 --> 17:38.658
I've stuck around
as long as I have.

17:40.393 --> 17:42.395
Mm.

17:44.063 --> 17:46.065
(Bruce chuckles softly)

17:50.270 --> 17:52.272
(knocking)

17:53.406 --> 17:56.209
(water running)

17:56.243 --> 17:58.478
(water stops)

18:08.621 --> 18:10.990
Ray. How are you?

18:11.023 --> 18:12.759
How come you didn't come
to the club?

18:12.792 --> 18:14.327
Yeah, sorry.

18:14.361 --> 18:16.963
Totally forgot.
My fault.

18:18.131 --> 18:20.500
So, you gonna invite me in
or...?

18:20.533 --> 18:22.802
Yeah, 'course.
Come in, come in.

18:25.805 --> 18:27.274
So, what's been happening?

18:27.307 --> 18:28.908
Oh, not much.

18:28.941 --> 18:30.510
What's been happening with you?

18:30.543 --> 18:32.845
Oh, mate, heaps, actually.
Yeah.

18:32.879 --> 18:35.081
I, um, had an audition
for a pilot yesterday.

18:35.114 --> 18:37.484
So, pretty stoked about that.

18:37.517 --> 18:39.252
-Like a TV show?
-Yeah.

18:39.286 --> 18:40.987
Oh.

18:41.020 --> 18:44.657
Yeah. It's, uh...

18:44.691 --> 18:46.826
You here for the dough?

18:46.859 --> 18:48.595
No, just thought I'd come around

18:48.628 --> 18:50.163
and see how your acting career
is going.

18:50.197 --> 18:51.931
(laughs)
Yeah.

18:51.964 --> 18:55.235
Uh, mate, I'm gonna have
to get that to you on Wednesday.

18:56.303 --> 18:57.837
Said you'd have the money, man.

18:57.870 --> 18:59.306
No, I know.
I know I did.

18:59.339 --> 19:01.374
And I'm sorry,
but I'm definitely gonna have it

19:01.408 --> 19:02.809
by Wednesday.
Definitely.

19:02.842 --> 19:04.677
(continues playing ukulele)

19:05.712 --> 19:08.147
I have to give you a touch-up.

19:09.316 --> 19:11.851
What? But Wednesday's
two days away.

19:11.884 --> 19:13.786
Yeah, I know when Wednesday is.

19:13.820 --> 19:15.455
(playing ukulele)

19:15.488 --> 19:16.789
Okay.

19:16.823 --> 19:18.191
Um...

19:18.225 --> 19:20.327
well, could it not be the face?

19:20.360 --> 19:21.394
It's got to be the face.

19:21.428 --> 19:22.729
Why?

19:22.762 --> 19:25.064
It's got to be somewhere
where people can see it.

19:25.097 --> 19:26.165
Why?

19:26.199 --> 19:27.367
So, if Freddy sees you,

19:27.400 --> 19:29.369
he knows I've done my job.

19:29.402 --> 19:31.804
(playing ukulele)

19:31.838 --> 19:33.373
Okay.

19:33.406 --> 19:34.574
Cool?

19:34.607 --> 19:36.209
-Yep.
-All right.

19:36.243 --> 19:38.177
Cool. All right.

19:38.211 --> 19:40.179
Don't-don't use my uke, please.

19:40.213 --> 19:42.081
My nan gave me that.

19:43.182 --> 19:45.151
(sighs)

19:45.184 --> 19:46.653
Happy?

19:46.686 --> 19:48.588
-Yeah.
-Cool.

19:48.621 --> 19:50.857
-Don't flinch, all right?
-(door closes)

19:50.890 --> 19:52.091
-(hammer cocks)
-Hey, whoa, whoa, whoa.

19:52.124 --> 19:54.193
Mate, mate, it's just my mum.
It's just my mum, okay?

19:54.227 --> 19:55.862
-Please. Pl...
-Why didn't you fucking
say something?

19:55.895 --> 19:58.231
She's staying with me
for a couple days.

19:58.265 --> 19:59.399
Please?

20:01.568 --> 20:03.836
Hello.

20:03.870 --> 20:05.204
How you doing?

20:05.238 --> 20:06.606
Mum, this is Ray.
He's a mate of mine.

20:06.639 --> 20:08.040
Hi. I'm Lorraine.

20:08.074 --> 20:09.942
Nice to meet you.

20:09.976 --> 20:11.944
Well, I'm gonna make a cuppa.

20:11.978 --> 20:13.446
Would you boys like one?

20:13.480 --> 20:16.048
Um...

20:16.082 --> 20:17.284
Yeah.

20:17.317 --> 20:19.952
Thanks, love.

20:19.986 --> 20:20.953
(cupboard door creaks open)

20:20.987 --> 20:22.555
(clinking)

20:22.589 --> 20:23.990
Mm-mmm.

20:28.961 --> 20:30.229
So, what do you do, Ray?

20:30.263 --> 20:31.731
Security, mainly.

20:31.764 --> 20:33.566
-Oh.
-Mm.

20:33.600 --> 20:35.268
So, you're just here
for a couple of days,

20:35.302 --> 20:36.903
-are you?
-Yes.

20:36.936 --> 20:39.138
I'm actually living
in Broken Hill at the moment.

20:39.171 --> 20:40.740
Been there a few years now.

20:40.773 --> 20:41.808
Oh, okay. Yeah.

20:41.841 --> 20:43.075
I went through there
a few years ago.

20:43.109 --> 20:44.076
Nice, uh...

20:44.110 --> 20:45.912
It's got a good feel to it.

20:45.945 --> 20:47.547
Yeah, it's nice.

20:47.580 --> 20:50.216
It's got a real community feel
about it, which I like.

20:50.249 --> 20:51.951
Yeah, well, you don't get much
of that around here, do you?

20:51.984 --> 20:53.219
No, you don't.

20:53.252 --> 20:56.423
-Mm.
-I lived in St Kilda
for many years,

20:56.456 --> 20:58.658
and there's very little
community spirit there,

20:58.691 --> 21:00.493
-I can tell you.
-Mm.

21:00.527 --> 21:02.662
Mm.

21:02.695 --> 21:05.432
Mm. We better get going.

21:05.465 --> 21:07.634
Oh, shit. Yeah.

21:07.667 --> 21:10.837
Um, we got to pick up my sister
from work, so...

21:12.271 --> 21:14.341
Actually, Mum,

21:14.374 --> 21:17.243
um, me and Ray--

21:17.276 --> 21:20.246
we've got to r-rehearse
for an audition I've got.

21:20.279 --> 21:21.981
-Oh, another one?
-Yeah.

21:22.014 --> 21:24.250
So... is that all right?

21:24.283 --> 21:25.985
Yeah. That's fine.

21:26.018 --> 21:27.420
I'll take my car.

21:27.454 --> 21:30.022
-JASON: Great.
-Oh. I'll get that door
for you, love.

21:32.191 --> 21:33.159
Nice to meet you.

21:33.192 --> 21:34.260
Nice to meet you, Ray.

21:34.293 --> 21:35.328
Okay.

21:35.362 --> 21:38.631
Oh, and... break a leg.

21:38.665 --> 21:40.900
I will. Thanks.

21:43.636 --> 21:45.271
Just-just not the teeth.

21:45.304 --> 21:47.306
Hey? I've just spent
eight grand on veneers.

21:47.340 --> 21:49.709
-Anything else?
-(sighs) No, that's it.

21:50.710 --> 21:52.945
Oh! Oh!

21:52.979 --> 21:54.447
Oh... I've got it!

21:54.481 --> 21:56.449
I've got it!
I've got the fucking money.

21:56.483 --> 21:58.017
(whimpers):
I've got it.

21:58.050 --> 21:59.285
Fuck!

21:59.318 --> 22:00.920
(groans)

22:01.921 --> 22:04.491
(groaning)

22:04.524 --> 22:06.926
(panting, groaning)

22:17.504 --> 22:18.971
Why didn't you just give me
the fucking money

22:19.005 --> 22:20.373
when I asked for it?

22:22.675 --> 22:25.244
I'm going to L.A.
for pilot season.

22:27.680 --> 22:29.148
No, you're not.

22:29.181 --> 22:30.249
No, no, no, no, no, no!

22:30.282 --> 22:32.351
("Beautiful People"
by Australian Crawl playing)

22:41.561 --> 22:44.597
* I said beautiful people *

22:44.631 --> 22:47.667
